      <section eId="sec_7_1_530">
        <num>7-1-530</num>
        <content>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1919, p. 135, art. 13, § 1; Code 1933, § 13-1401; Ga. L. 1973, p. 278, § 1; Code 1933, § 41A-2401, enacted by Ga. L. 1974, p. 705, § 1; Ga. L. 1996, p. 848, § 8; Ga. L. 1997, p. 485, § 17; Ga. L. 2000, p. 174, § 11; Ga. L. 2001, p. 970, § 5; Ga. L. 2003, p. 843, § 6; Ga. L. 2007, p. 502, § 4/SB 70; Ga. L. 2016, p. 390, § 2-7/HB 811; Ga. L. 2020, p. 320, § 4/HB 781; Ga. L. 2021, p. 323, § 7/HB 111.)</p>
          <p>The 2020 amendment,
      effective January 1, 2021, in the first sentence of subsection (a), substituted "a trust company" for "an institution exercising trust powers alone" and "with a bank that is authorized to exercise trust powers so long as the resulting institution is a bank" for "only with another such trust company".</p>
          <p>The 2021 amendment,
      effective July 1, 2021, deleted "involving one or more banks or trust companies" following "across state lines" in subsection (d); and rewrote subsection (f), which read: "As used in this part, the term 'share exchange' means a plan of exchange of all of the outstanding shares of one or more classes or series of shares in accordance with this part."</p>
        </content>
